The problem with most SF mini-images is that the games are regional. So if you have a mini-image made for a European version, it won't work with a US version.

That's been my painful experience with trying to get V8 Supercars 2 to work with DTM/Toca Race Driver 2 images.

Daemon-tools and Alcohol120% are both blacklisted by the StarForce3 protection, and that's why it won't allow mounting with mini-image.
And you only have to match the serial with the right regional mini-image, the content is the same. But wait for D-tools 4 for a patch to the blacklist!
